Description: # Micropie
        
        Micropie is a asynchronous micro framework to build microservices inspired by
        [nameko](https://www.nameko.io/) focused on simplicity configurability and scalability.
        
        
        ### Installing
        To install *micropie* just run
        ``` text
        pip install micropie
        ```
        
        ### Quick start
        Define your service class
        ```python
        class Person:
            
            def get_full_name(self):
                # your function body here ...
                pass
        ```
        
        Assuming that your class is in file called *person.py* run your service as follow
        ```text
        micropie person:Person
        ```
        Or from `python` code as
        ```text
        micropie.run(Person)
        ```
        
        An output like this is showed if all was okay
        ```text
        =======================
             MICROPIE v0.0.0
        =======================
         * pid: 147563
         * standalone: True
         * service: person
         * description: 
         * instance: 8dea5f67bc2849ff9ec5e7934f5b1ad5
         * transport: tcp
         * loop: auto
         * logs: INFO
        2020-09-23 18:07:09,063 (micropie.service) [INFO]: STARTED listen on: tcp://0.0.0.0:39523 (Press CTRL+C to quit)
        ```
        
        To read full documentation visit [micropie docs](https://micropie.io/docs)
        
